THE GAME
--------

  'Quador' is a Workbench game where you rotate, in a clockwise
manner, 4 neighbouring tiles: the clicked tile, the tile located
at the right, the tile located one row below at right and the tile
located under the clicked tile. The goal is to make alignments of
4 coloured tiles or more of the same type horizontally, vertically
or both at the same time. The more tiles of the same type there
are, the more points you get. One thing you must keep in mind is
that if there are less than 4 remaining tiles of a type, the game
ends... unless some 'neutral blocks' are present on the game
board...

  A particularity of the game is that when you line up 4 or more
tiles of the same type, they are then removed and are replaced
with small square neutral blocks. This can help, especially if
there are few of one type of tiles... As the blocks 'grow' one
size for each move you make, when they reach their maximum size,
they are replaced with new coloured tiles.

  Have fun!

